WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.279 --> 00:00:07.609
THIS WEEK AT INTERIOR…

00:00:07.609 --> 00:00:12.150
ONE MILLION DOLLARS IN ADDITIONAL FUNDING
ANNOUNCED THIS WEEK FOR THE SAN DIEGO NATIONAL

00:00:12.150 --> 00:00:14.440
WILDLIFE REFUGE COMPLEX…

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:19.140
SAN DIEGO TOOK THE TOP SPOT IN A NATIONWIDE
COMPETITION LAUNCHED IN MARCH TO HELP ENGAGE

00:00:19.140 --> 00:00:21.509
NEW AND DIVERSE YOUTH IN THE GREAT OUTDOORS.

00:00:21.509 --> 00:00:27.680
WE KNOW THAT WE HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY IN A PLACE
LIKE THIS TO HAVE A CONNECTION WHERE KIDS

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:28.910
DON’T HAVE TO GO FAR.

00:00:28.910 --> 00:00:31.770
THEY CAN COME JUST REALLY ACROSS THE STREET
FROM SOME OF THEIR SCHOOLS, AND BE RIGHT IN

00:00:31.770 --> 00:00:33.500
A WILDLIFE REFUGE.

00:00:33.500 --> 00:00:39.770
PEOPLE THAT ARE GOING TO CARE ABOUT THE OUTDOORS...PEOPLE
THAT ARE GOING TO LOOK FOR CAREERS IN THE

00:00:39.770 --> 00:00:44.920
OUTDOORS...PEOPLE THAT ARE GOING TO BECOME
ACTIVE CITIZENS WHO ARE CONCERNED ABOUT THE

00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.550
PLANET AND THE FUTURE.

00:00:46.550 --> 00:00:51.019
SECRETARY JEWELL SAYS HELPING KIDS FEEL WELCOME
ON PUBLIC LANDS AT A YOUNG AGE CAN SPARK A

00:00:51.019 --> 00:00:55.039
PASSION TO BE GOOD STEWARDS OF NATURE THAT
WILL LAST A LIFETIME.

00:00:55.039 --> 00:00:59.949
AS WILDFIRE SEASON AND AN EPIC DROUGHT CONTINUE
IN THE GOLDEN STATE, THE SECRETARY STOPPED

00:00:59.949 --> 00:01:04.519
IN REDDING CALIFORNIA TO MEET WITH MEMBERS
OF THE INTERAGENCY FIRE LEADERSHIP TEAM…

00:01:04.519 --> 00:01:08.590
SHE ALSO MET WITH EMPLOYEES OF THE BUREAU
OF LAND MANAGEMENT, THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE,

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:12.380
THE BUREAU OF RECLAMATION, THE U-S FOREST
SERVICE AND CALFIRE.

00:01:12.380 --> 00:01:17.200
NEARLY A DOZEN SIGNIFICANT WILDFIRES ARE NOW
BLAZING IN CALIFORNIA, CURRENTLY UNDER A STATE

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:18.270
OF EMERGENCY.

00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:21.899
THE SECRETARY PRAISED THE FIREFIGHTERS’
COORDINATION AND PROFESSIONALISM…

00:01:21.899 --> 00:01:27.049
SHE ALSO REITERATED HER SUPPORT FOR THE PRESIDENT’S
BUDGET PROPOSAL, WHICH SHE SAYS PROVIDES BETTER

00:01:27.049 --> 00:01:31.910
FLEXIBILITY DURING PEAK FIRE SEASON, WITHOUT
ADDING TO THE DEFICIT OR FORCING CUTBACKS

00:01:31.910 --> 00:01:35.920
IN OTHER PROGRAMS LIKE FOREST AND RANGELAND
RESTORATION.

00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:40.000
THE BUREAU OF OCEAN ENERGY MANAGEMENT THIS
WEEK ANNOUNCED THAT THREE AREAS OFF THE COAST

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.850
OF NORTH CAROLINA HAVE BEEN DEFINED FOR POTENTIAL
COMMERCIAL WIND ENERGY DEVELOPMENT.

00:01:44.850 --> 00:01:47.899
TOGETHER THE SITES TOTAL MORE THAN 300-THOUSAND
ACRES..

00:01:47.899 --> 00:01:51.900
IT’S ALL PART OF THE PRESIDENT’S CLIMATE
ACTION PLAN TO CREATE AMERICAN JOBS, DEVELOP

00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:55.520
DOMESTIC CLEAN ENERGY SOURCES, AND CUT CARBON
POLLUTION.

00:01:55.520 --> 00:02:00.000
THE POTENTIAL SITES OFF THE NORTH CAROLINA
COAST JOIN A GROWING LIST OF SITES ALREADY

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.289
IN WIND ENERGY DEVELOPMENT PHASES, FROM NEW
ENGLAND TO THE MID ATLANTIC.

00:02:04.289 --> 00:02:09.760
THE SECRETARY THIS WEEK ALSO JOINED ENERGY
SECRETARY ERNEST MONIZ IN SANTE FE, NEW MEXICO,

00:02:09.760 --> 00:02:15.159
TO RECEIVE STAKEHOLDER INPUT TO THE QUADRENNIAL
ENERGY REVIEW, AN ADMINISTRATION-WIDE EFFORT

00:02:15.159 --> 00:02:20.540
TO MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS REGARDING KEY INFRASTRUCTURE
NEEDED FOR TRANSMISSION, STORAGE AND DISTRIBUTION

00:02:20.540 --> 00:02:21.560
OF ENERGY.

00:02:21.560 --> 00:02:25.420
THE SANTA FE MEETING EXAMINED STATE, LOCAL
AND TRIBAL ENERGY ISSUES.

00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:31.390
AND INTERIOR HAS A NEW CHIEF INFORMATION OFFICER
THIS WEEK, WITH THE SELECTION OF SYLVIA BURNS.

00:02:31.390 --> 00:02:34.790
BURNS HAD BEEN ACTING CIO SINCE MARCH OF THIS
YEAR.

00:02:34.790 --> 00:02:36.540
THAT’S THIS WEEK, AT INTERIOR.

